02/03/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- Police found a 2.5-kilogram explosive device near a police station in Presevo, southern Serbia, on Saturday (1 March). The bomb was placed on a fence separating the station from a school. Presevo's mayor condemned the incident as the work of the darkest elements of society. The device, described as a time bomb, was discovered less than 30 minutes before it was to explode. (AP, AFP, Tanjug, B92 - 01/03/03)
